The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 29: Members of the Abhijit Sen committee were divided on banning futures trade in the absence of any conclusive evidence on prices being influenced by forward trading. While Sen, chairman of the committee, favoured the continuation of the ban on rice, wheat, tur and urad, other members felt that the ban was not a solution to deal with price volatility. The committee, which submitted its report today, noted that Indian data analysed in this report does not show any clear evidence of either reduced or increased volatility of spot prices because of futures trading.                            
	 Brussels, April 29: ArcelorMittal has signed a deal to buy iron ore from Brazilian miner Vale for the next 10 years. It did not disclose how much it would pay Vale to buy 480 million tonnes of iron ore and pellets for its steel plants, but called it the worlds largest-ever deal between a steel company and an iron ore supplier.                            
	 Mumbai, April 29: Sesa Goa Limited, a subsidiary of Vedanta Resources and Indias largest exporter of iron ore, has announced a bonus issue and a stock split. The Sesa Goa board has proposed the issue of bonus shares in the ratio of one equity share for every one equity held in the existing share capital.                             
	 New Delhi, April 29: Bhel and NTPC have formed a joint venture and announced an investment of Rs 5,000 crore in the next five years to undertake power and infrastructure projects. NTPC-Bhel power projects, the joint venture company will be located at a port-based facility either in Andhra Pradesh or Maharashtra.                            
	 Mumbai, April 29: 3i Infotech will acquire the US-based Regulus group LLC for $100 million. The company has signed an agreement with Regulus Group under which it will acquire a 100 per cent stake the company.                            
	 Beijing, April 29: China has said it would study suggestions made by Pakistan and Iran on including it in the Iran-Pakistan-India gas pipeline project.                             
	 Mumbai, April 29: The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) has exempted corporates from seeking prior permission of the central government for international competitive bidding in forex to boost Indian Incs participation in global bidding.                            
	 Mumbai, April 29: Mukesh Ambani-led Reliance Industries Ltd (RIL) has asked Bombay High Court to revoke a stay on the sale of gas from the Krishna-Godavari basin. RIL contends that the high courts stay makes it impossible to excavate gas.                                                                                                                         
